description: An object that serves as registration for a Synapse user to receive events for the specified event.

webhookId.description: The ID associated with the Webhook.

objectId.description: The ID of the Synapse object to receive events of.

objectType.description: Which type is Synapse object is associated with the Webhook.

userId.description: The ID of the Synapse user who has registered to receive this webhook event.

invokeEndpoint.description: The endpoint the Synapse user would like the webhook events sent to on invocation. Must be 256 Characters or less.

isVerified.description: True if Synapse has confirmed the validity of the Webhook invokeEndpoint. False if Synapse has determined the invokeEndpoint is invalid.

isWebhookEnabled.description: True if the Synapse user has selected to receive events. If the user sets to false, events will be temporalily paused.

isAuthenticationEnabled.description: True if the Synapse user has opted in to require authorization to receive the webhook invocation POST request. In this case, a JWT token will be included in the invocation. False otherwise: no authorization will be required and no JWT token included in the invocation.

etag.description: Synapse employs an Optimistic Concurrency Control (OCC) scheme to handle concurrent updates. Since the E-Tag changes every time an Webhook is updated it is used to detect when a client's current representation of an Webhook is out-of-date.

createdOn.description: The date this webhook was created.

modifiedOn.description: The date this webhook was last modified.

createdBy.description: The ID of the user that created this webhook.

modifiedBy.description: The ID of the user that last modified this webhook.
